WEBVTT

NOTE
HealthPulse Edge — demo subtitles, target 2:30 cut.
Adjust timestamps to your actual cut. Voice text aligns to docs/VIDEO-SCRIPT.md.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.000
1,350 hospitals in the US have the same federal CMS reporting obligations as Mayo Clinic.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:18.000
No IT department. No analytics team. A tribal council policy that forbids patient data leaving the reservation.

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:25.000
This is one of them. Sage Mesa Critical Access Hospital, Window Rock, Arizona.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:32.000
Gemma 4 runs on the Mac Mini under the desk. There's no internet connection right now.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:40.000
Marlene is the RN, the quality officer, and the EHR admin. Tuesdays she runs the federal reports.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:50.000
She types: "find the top three care gaps." Gemma 4 fans out three function calls. Four seconds later:

00:00:50.000 --> 00:01:00.000
"Your sepsis bundle compliance is the lowest in your CMS region. Refresh the bundle education. Audit antibiotic timing."

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:08.000
Stanford-grade quality analytics. Four seconds. On a $400 box. Airplane mode on.

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:18.000
She has three weeks of handwritten patient experience surveys nobody has entered.

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:28.000
Gemma 4 vision sees the form locally, transcribes it, adds it to local FHIR. PHI egress: false. Signed.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:38.000
Quarter-end. CMS reporting is due. Sovereignty Mode demands a tribal council co-signature key.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:48.000
She pastes the key. Redaction sub-agent strips 142 PHI fields. Differential privacy noise applied.

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:58.000
The envelope is signed with a SHA-256 hash the hospital itself cannot retroactively forge.

00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:08.000
CMS gets the aggregate. The patients get to stay anonymous. The tribal council gets a cryptographic receipt.

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:18.000
Frontier intelligence does not require a frontier datacenter.

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:28.000
With Gemma 4, the smallest hospital in America can do what only the largest could yesterday.

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:30.000
HealthPulse Edge. github.com/sgharlow/gemma-health.
